  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 310 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Cut @fingerling potatoes{12%ounce} into 1-inch pieces. Pick fronds from @dill{¼%ounce} and discard stems. Finely chop fronds until you have 1 TBSP. Finely chop @parsley{¼%ounce}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Zest @lemon{1} until you have ½ tsp zest, then cut into wedges.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with a pinch of @salt{} and enough water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes are easily pierced by a fork, about ~{15%minutes}. Drain, then return to pot.

Meanwhile, toss @broccoli florets{8%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast in oven until beginning to turn bright green, about ~{5%minutes} (we'll be adding more items to the sheet later).

In a #small bowl{}, combine parsley, lemon zest, @panko breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, half the garlic, a pinch of salt and pepper, and a drizzle of olive oil. Pat @cod fillets{12%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{}, then brush fillets with a drizzle of olive oil. Season all over with salt and pepper.

After broccoli has roasted 5 minutes, remove baking sheet from oven. Give broccoli a toss and push toward one side. Place cod on other side of sheet. Brush a thin layer of @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon} onto tops of fillets, then press crust mixture into mustard. Return sheet to oven and cook until broccoli is tender and cod is cooked through and flakes easily, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Add @butter{1%tablespoon}, remaining garlic, and dill to pot with potatoes. Heat over medium heat and toss until butter is melted and garlic is fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Divide potatoes, broccoli, and cod between plates. Serve with lemon wedges on the side for squeezing over.